*Soaring, soaring.... the little kitten soared through the air, curled in a 
ball, flying head over heels into the great blue unknown. Her little red 
bat-wings blowing in the wind, she began to flap them against the current. 
Faster and faster he flapped, and slower and slower hesoared, until he was 
hovering in mid-air, his wings going a million miles per hour. But exhastion 
and dizzyness swept over her and she stopped flaping her tiny wings, and she 
began the long plumett to Earth, her wings, fur and tail streaming behind 
her. Her little head pointed to Earth, she gained speed until she hit 
super-sonic, leaving the sound of her fall behing her, far behind. Her lips 
where now flapping in the great preasures that built while she was falling. 
She peeked through her eyes, to find she was going to hit a shiny round 
head, Dinobots head to be exact.........*
